{
  "text": "The most important parameter determining the quantum of the influence due to shunting is the magnitude of the shunt or in simple terms, the value of the shunt resistance offered by the PV cell. The value of the shunt resistance offered by the PV cell is in turn determined by the shunt resistance offered by the shunted region of the PV cell and area of the shunted region. To have a realistic picture of the severity of shunting and the resulting mismatch, a shunt resistance of 1 Ohm has been chosen for the shunted area, whose value has been selected based on the published literature [CITATION_1] .",
